What is Emmet?

Emmet is a plugin for many popular text editors which greatly improves HTML and css workflow.

we can use short expression to generate HTML markup and css.

./././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././ 

Difference between a Library and Framework?

Library: A library provides functions or modules that you can call directly in your code to perform specific tasks. You control when and how to use it.

Framework: A framework provides a structured foundation for building applications. It dictatesthe overall architecture and flow of the application, often with predefined conventions and patterns. You fit your code into the framework's structure.

dictates-:(an order of principle that must be obeyed) 

