What is crossorigin in script tag?

The crossorigin attribute in a <script> tag is used to specify how the browser should handle requests for cross-origin resources (i.e., resources hosted on a different domain, protocol, or port than the current page).

Cross-Origin Resource Sharing (CORS) is a mechanism that supports secure requests and data transfers from outside origins (domain, scheme, or port). 
For example, example.com uses a text font that's hosted on fonts.com . When visiting example.com , the user's browser will make a request for the font from fonts.com .

./././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././ 

What is diference between React and ReactDOM?

 React is the core library for building user interfaces in React applications, ReactDOM is a package that handles the rendering of React components in the browser's DOM. They work together to create interactive and dynamic web applications using React.

./././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././ 


What is difference between react.development.js and react.production.js files via CDN?

react.development.js is used during development for debugging and development-specific features so it will take time to load , while react.production.js is optimized for production use with a focus on performance and smaller file size in that it will remove all logs and warrnings and development specificfeatures.


./././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././././ 

What is async and defer?

Use async for scripts that can be executed independently and don't need to wait for the DOM or other scripts.
Use defer for scripts that need to be executed after the DOM has been fully parsed but before the DOMContentLoaded event is fired.

